Today, the United States marks a tragic milestone of one million lives lost to COVID-19. This pandemic has left behind empty chairs at dinner tables and has forever changed families, communities, and the nation. Jill and Joe Biden express their prayers for those who are grieving and understand the pain of losing a loved one. They remind the nation not to grow numb to this sorrow and emphasize the importance of remaining vigilant against the pandemic. They call on Congress to sustain resources such as testing, vaccines, and treatments. The Bidens urge Americans to draw strength from each other and assure that together, as the United States of America, we can overcome this challenge. They conclude by praying for the one million lives lost and their loved ones.